interactions.input: Who can apply to Alpha Venture DAO?
interactions.response: Alpha Venture DAO is open to Web3 Founders who are building DeFi projects.

interactions.input: What is the due diligence process for applications?

The process includes evaluating the application, an introductory call, one or two deep dive calls, and communicating the final decision via email.

responses: Alpha Venture DAO is a community of daring individuals who shape the future of Web3 by reinventing how decentralized applications (dApps) are built, contributed, and owned. Together with our network of Web3 industry leaders and community, we build and incubate Web3 innovation in order to become a massive ecosystem of dApps that captures value regardless of which chains or sectors dominate Web3 in the future. Alpha Venture DAO is made up of 2 parts: build and incubate. As builders ourselves, we will continue to ‘build’ cutting-edge products across multiple chains and verticals. We will also ‘incubate’ new innovations to the crypto space and assist Web3 builders to grow their projects from 0-to-1 and 1-to-100 with the support from our community and Alpha Network.

Web3 builders from anywhere in the world can apply to Alpha Venture DAO. We offer two programs that cater to different stages: Build and Launch. Build Track is for early stage projects with team, product ideas, and a reasonable protocol architecture / design including protocol components, flow & interactions. Launch Track is for mid to late stage projects that have a workable product and have raised a small funding round, but have yet to launch on mainnet or yet to launch the token.

The due diligence process for applications to Alpha Venture DAO consists of four phases. In phase one, we evaluate the application. In phase two, we have an introductory call with you to understand your motivation, progress, and how Alpha Venture DAO can help. In phase three, we have one or two deep dive calls into the product, target customers, and technical aspects. In phase four, we communicate the final decision to you via email. The complete process from receiving the application to making a final decision is up to 4 weeks.
